---
name: scljet-sql-no-from
description: SclJet SQL SELECT without FROM — scalar expression evaluation (one computed row); matches reference sqlite3
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet SQL SELECT without FROM

`SELECT <exprs>` with no `FROM` returns a single computed row — the full expression engine evaluated
against an empty row: arithmetic, `||`, functions, `CASE`, `%`, comparisons. Every result is
byte-identical to reference sqlite3 running the same SQL (verified out-of-band); locked across backends.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(id INTEGER)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L)))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db) =>
    show(db, "SELECT 1 + 1")
    show(db, "SELECT 2 * 3 + 4")
    show(db, "SELECT UPPER('hello')")
    show(db, "SELECT LENGTH('scljet')")
    show(db, "SELECT 'a' || 'b' || 'c'")
    show(db, "SELECT CASE WHEN 5 > 3 THEN 'yes' ELSE 'no' END")
    show(db, "SELECT 10 % 3")
    show(db, "SELECT SUBSTR('hello world', 7)")
    show(db, "SELECT 5 > 3")
```
